Date of Birth: February 23, 1861<br/>
Birthplace: Farmington, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 9, 1906<br/>
Death: August 8, 1950<br/>
<br/>
Born Feb. 23, 1861, at Farmington, Davis Co., Utah, to Franklin Dewey Richards and Nanny Longstroth. Ordained apostle April 9, 1906, by Joseph F. Smith, at age 45; sustained as acting Patriarch to the Church Oct. 8,1937; released from this position Oct. 3, 1942; sustained as president of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles May 21, 1945; died Aug. 8, 1950, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 89.